HEADWORD: Harrisia
<hw>Harrisia</hw> <pos>prop. n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A genus of
slender often treelike spiny cacti with solitary showy nocturnal white
or pink flowers; Florida and Caribbean to South America.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> genus <gen>Harrisia</gen>.</syn>⟦br⟧
